==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} {{term|inflatio|īnflātiō|expansion, blowing up|lang=la}}, from {{term|inflatus|īnfātus|lang=la}}, the perfect passive participle of {{term|inflo|īnflō|blow into, expand}}, from {{term|in||into|lang=la}} + {{term|flo|flō|blow|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act, instance of, or state of expansion or increase in size, especially by injection of a gas.
#: ''The '''inflation''' of the balloon took five hours.''
# {{economics}} A increase in the general level of prices or in the [[cost of living]].
# {{economics}} A decline in the value of [[money]].
# Undue expansion or increase, as of academic grades.
# {{context|cosmology}} An extremely rapid expansion of the universe, theorised to have occurred very shortly after the [[big bang]].

